# 🤖 Support Agent — LangGraph + Supabase

A production-ready **LangGraph** workflow that acts as a customer support agent. It parses a free-text support request, extracts the customer name and product ID, queries a **Supabase PostgreSQL** database for the product's current status, and replies with a natural-language response powered by **Gemini**.

---

## Workflow Overview

```
User Input
    │
    ▼
┌─────────────┐
│   extract   │  LLM extracts user_name + product_id from free text
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
┌─────────────┐
│  validate   │  Checks product_id was found; sets error if missing
└──────┬──────┘
       │
  ┌────┴────┐
  │         │
  ▼         ▼ (error → skip DB)
┌───────────┐
│fetch_prod │  Queries Supabase products table by ID
└─────┬─────┘
      │
      ▼
┌─────────────┐
│   respond   │  LLM drafts a friendly reply based on status + note
└──────┬──────┘
       │
       ▼
    Response
```

### Nodes

| Node | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `extract` | Uses Gemini to parse `user_name` and `product_id` from raw input |
| `validate` | Ensures `product_id` was extracted; routes to `respond` on error |
| `fetch_product` | Calls Supabase and retrieves `status` + `note` for the product |
| `respond` | Generates a natural-language reply; handles all error paths gracefully |

### Product Statuses

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `pending` | Not started yet |
| `in_progress` | Currently being worked on |
| `done` | Completed successfully |
| `stopped` | Halted, no longer active |

---

## Project Structure

```
support_agent/
├── agent.py              # LangGraph graph definition + nodes
├── state.py              # SupportState TypedDict
├── tools.py              # Supabase check_product_status tool
├── requirements.txt      # Runtime dependencies
├── requirements-dev.txt  # Dev/test dependencies
├── .env.example          # Environment variable template
├── tests/
│   ├── conftest.py       # Pytest path setup
│   └── test_agent.py     # Full test suite (all mocked)
└── .github/
    └── workflows/
        └── ci.yml        # GitHub Actions CI pipeline
```

